<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <head>No. 34.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Jay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-01"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 1,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 218.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch, No. 429, of
                            the 8th ultimo, and to previous correspondence in regard to the World’s
                            Exposition to be held <pb facs="0151" n="55" xml:id="pg_55"/> at Vienna
                            in 1873, I have now to state in reply that the subject has been
                            presented to Congress, and now awaits the action of that body.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>